      "writtenOn": "2026-06-10T12:49:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Restore is the only reachable-correct option here, and this is deliberate: with push disabled or token cleared there is no FCM wakeup path at all, so deactivating (as suggested) would leave the user unreachable for calls and messages indefinitely — precisely the merge-blocking issue raised on PS15 in this same branch, which PS16 fixed by restoring. Permanently-active accounts in background is the historical, pre-patch behavior for every non-push configuration: when the user disables push they opt into persistent connections; the battery optimization only applies when FCM can replace them. The restore also clears the recorded set, so no stale optimization state lingers (re-entering the optimization requires a future background transition with push available, which re-records correctly).",
      "parentUuid": "8a3736fb_b52e9314",
      "revId": "fcef5e054d3d7f58fc67112b11fca888cf4d8a07",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
