      "writtenOn": "2026-06-10T12:49:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Line 180: The lifecycle observer is added every time `onCreate()` runs, but there is no guard against duplicate registration if the application object is recreated in tests or by custom initialization paths. Duplicate observers would schedule duplicate restore/deactivation work and make timing-dependent behavior harder to reason about. Store the observer in a property or guard registration with a boolean.",
      "revId": "fcef5e054d3d7f58fc67112b11fca888cf4d8a07",
