      "writtenOn": "2026-06-10T12:49:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 86: `notePushReceived()` is called before `restoreProxyAccountsAfterBackground()`, but both enqueue work on different executors/loopers. The deactivation grace timestamp is protected on the main looper, while account restoration is queued on the daemon executor, so under load the 5-second deactivation runnable can fire before restoration/reconnection actually starts. That can immediately deactivate accounts again and still drop the incoming call negotiation. Consider scheduling the grace window after the restore command is queued/completed, or expose a single application-level method that serializes note+restore+deactivation scheduling in a deterministic order.",
      "revId": "fcef5e054d3d7f58fc67112b11fca888cf4d8a07",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
