      "writtenOn": "2026-06-10T12:49:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 611: The restore path unconditionally reactivates any recorded proxy-enabled account without checking whether the account was explicitly deactivated while the app was in the background. `setAccountActive(accountId, false)` removes the id from `backgroundDeactivatedAccounts`, but that operation is queued on the same executor; if a foreground/push restore was queued first, the restore can run before the explicit deactivation and briefly/reactively undo the user\u0027s requested inactive state. Check the current active/enabled state or make explicit user deactivation synchronously mark the id before queuing daemon work so a stale restore cannot win the queue ordering.",
